article.headline: Brown 84, Dartmouth 64
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Brown's Jason Forte scored 23 points to lead the Bears to an 84-64 victory over Dartmouth on Saturday night. The Bears' (10-11, 6-2 ) Patrick Powers had 22 points, along with 12 rebounds, while Mike Martin scored 18. Jaime Kilburn added 17 as Brown shot 52.8 percent from the floor. Dartmouth (3-19, 1-7) held a 38-30 lead when Scott Klingbeil had a layup with four minutes to go in the first half. The Bears answered with a 13-0 run, including three-point baskets by Forte, Martin and Powers, for a 43-38 halftime advantage. Brown had a double-digit lead, 54-34, on a pair of Powers free throws at the 14:05 mark, and was able to maintain it until Steve Callahan's three-point basket with five minutes to play. That got Dartmouth within eight, 65-57, before Brown built it back to double figures. Callahan led the Big Green with 15 points.
